The fluoropropyl group is attached at the 3-position of the octane ring, and the nitrogen atom is located at the 8-position of the bicyclic structure. The SMILES notation provides a concise and standardized way to represent the chemical structure of complex molecules for computational analysis and data sharing within the scientific community.
